<font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugadianten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gadianten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 1:33:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23918.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Respect for Rogues</span><hr size=1> I was in the OT zone last night and a buncha bored people began a litte give and take in shouts and OOC.<br><br>Everyone was bragging about their class. Some were making fun of others. When someone said:<br><br>Player_01 shouts &quot;Rangers &gt; all!!&quot;<br>Player_02 shouts &quot;YEA! Rangers kick everyones @$$!!&quot;<br><br>Gadianten says in out of character &quot;Duel me&quot;<br><br>Player_01 shouts &quot;Lvl and class?&quot;<br><br>Gadianten says in out of character &quot;40 Rogue&quot;<br><br>**Silence<br><br>**Crickets<br><br>**A Kunark Rhino bellows in the distance<br><br>**Silence<br><br>Player_01 tells you &quot;I'm only lvl 38&quot;<br><br>Me &quot;Thats close enough, plus you have all those spells!&quot;<br><br>Player_01 tells you &quot;And you'll go invis on me, no way!&quot;<br><br>Me &quot; But you're an ubah Rangah! = ) &quot;<br><br>I've never dueled with my Rogue, but is Hide that brutal in a duel? I can only imagine that it would be.<br><br>How do Rogues usually fair in duels?<br><br>On a PvP server doesn't really count though, I play a lot on Sullon and everyone is always geared for pvp action. But on a blue server it's spontaneous.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urazzbuten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razzbuten</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 2:14:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23918.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Respect for Rogues</span><hr size=1> Regardless of the char I am playing at that moment rarely ever is a dual turned down regardless of class.  I don't have a rogue over 20, but I would pit myself at ya with any other char.  Espcially a ranger.  They can do the same to you with Camo, not to mention keep you running with SOW.  Snare you and have some fun...But I try to keep a bracer of the hidden ready for these situations too!.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utolanin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tolanin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 2:15:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23918.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Respect for Rogues</span><hr size=1> Rogue vs most classes = a dead rogue maybe you could beat a warrior but prolly not.  Hide is ok until about lv 30 when most classes either get see invis or an item with it..  Ranger has sow and decent ranged dmg.  In most duels its just a kite anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerilyana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerilyana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 2:21:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23918.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> respect</span><hr size=1> Well, as long as they don't research rogues, they'll be deathly scared of the backstab, unless they're pvp vets. If you expect to be dueling 40th level newbs (and how they retain their ignorance to that level is beyond me), be sure to stock up on some fun poisons, like spine break or some other paralyzing stuff.<br><br>If you haven't done it in the pass, switch camera views around some when you are fighting and evade to see the effect. Your opponent should still have a lock on you, but visually you will disappear. If you have sow and you tie sneak to the evade function, you virtually are hidden. Just back away so his swings don't break your hiding.<br><br>There are some good pvp guides floating around. Essentially expect your opponent to quick buff himself or from his group, as well as finding the nearest wall he can find to put his back to. If he's smart, he'll find a thick wall since you can usually backstab through if he's up against it.<br><br>Rogues lack buffing ability but in a prolonged fight, we can outdamage a warrior type 1on1. They fear the hidden backstab initially and the up close quick circling (if you have mastered the mouse look function). Use a bow at distance if he is doing the back to wall thing. Be sure to have a set of dueling arrows built for range to yank him to you. Then get in close and go to town. If he's using a 2h weap, you can probably time it so you slip in close to get a few hits, pull back and watch him miss his swing and then rush in for a few more, but I would personally just try and stay on his back. Mobs get the benefit of auto-tracking, but twitchy human players should be no problem.<br><br>This isn't the guide to dueling, just a taste of options available to you should you find yourself in a hormone stockpiled zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 2:46:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23918.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: respect</span><hr size=1> A succesful evade will remove you fromt the target window, unless player has See Invis up.  o See Invis and you can avoid damage while waiting for those perfect BS shots.<br><br>Keep pumice or Golem wand handy to get rid of snare or to clear pesky damage shields, which rack up fast due to your low delay weapons.<br><br>Poisons are great when they stick, but since you will only have one opportunity at the beggining of the fight to use them, they cannot be relied upon.<br><br>Rogues can be very deadly opponents.  Takes a little more skill to master than most other classes and there is no room for error. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uroguepitts.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoguePitts</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 2:55:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23918.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: respect</span><hr size=1> If he snares ya, dont plan on winning <p>Pitts<br>52 Rogue of the Divine Legion<br>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrezdian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krezdian</A></span><br>